2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper uses common-sense knowledge in the form of scripts to improve the model's estimates of human predictions. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper builds a computational model for prediction. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper may discuss the complexity of the model or the computational resources required for the experiments. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also less likely but possible as the paper may use neural networks or evolutionary algorithms in the model building process.
